            "description": "\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Technical CRM Manager (m/f/d)</strong></p>\n<p>Miami, Florida / Denver, CO / <strong>Remote</strong></p>\n<p>audibene / hear.com is the fastest-growing hearing care company ever. We are driven by our belief that every person should hear well to live well. With our unique digital business model, we have changed the way hearing care is provided. We are a profitable global health-technology company with origins in Europe. Since starting our journey in 2012, we have helped over 100,000 customers get on the path to better hearing. In just 7 years we have grown our team from 2 to over 1,000 people. We work hard and play hard in 11 international locations from Denver to Seoul.</p>\n<p>We promise to ourselves: to define the future of hearing care, to never be corporate and to always live Day One. Join us now, as we are shaping this fascinating consumer healthcare space!</p>\n<p>We are looking for a Technical CRM Manager (Salesforce Marketing Cloud) (m/f/d) based in Denver (CO) or Miami (Florida) or 100% Remote.</p>\n<p><strong>The position:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creation, maintenance and execution of campaigns, journeys, automations and processes</li>\n<li>Design and document technical CRM solutions based on business needs (including email, SMS and API connections)</li>\n<li>Daily administration, troubleshooting and technical support for the salesforce org</li>\n<li>Responsible for the effective run and ongoing support of the CRM integration platform based on Microsoft SQL data base</li>\n<li>Maintenance of users, profiles, roles and permission sets</li>\n<li>Train new and existing users on system functionality</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Your profile:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong technical understanding of business / marketing processes</li>\n<li>Experienced in technical administration of CRM systems</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of SQL, JavaScript, SSJS, HTML</li>\n<li>Close attention to detail and excellent analytical skills, able to explain complicated procedures</li>\n<li>Ability to quickly identify and integrate more efficient workflows and processes, find and fix errors</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Our Perks:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>With your task at audibene you help people to improve their living situation. We all enjoy to go to work for a good purpose.</li>\n<li>We live a dynamic and challenging as well as open minded environment: share and discuss your knowledges, make suggestions and try something new – lets just do it!</li>\n<li>We are looking for people that want to grow and make an impact in technology @ audibene.</li>\n<li>We live a flexible working hour and home-office model (culture of trust).</li>\n<li>Relocation bonus: we pay a nice relocation bonus, if you want to move to Berlin.</li>\n<li>Be part of an international team that makes a difference in hundreds of peoples’ lives every year. We are more than 50 nationalities and we speak more than 20 languages. You can learn any of them in our Language Tandem program and also join our German courses!</li>\n<li>Apart from the usual benefits, as free coffee, drinks and healthy snacks, we focus mainly on our people, hence we love to spend time together on regular team events, parties and annual trips.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is a&nbsp;full-time&nbsp;position based in&nbsp;Denver (CO) or Miami (Florida) or 100% Remote<strong>.</strong> If you want to be part of a young, dynamic and fast growing company, a new challenge awaits you!</p>\n\t\t",
            "date": "2019-12-23"
